Date: Thu, 26 Feb 2026 12:03:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix insecure deserialization vulnerability by replacing
 pickle with JSON

Replaced `pickle` with `json` for saving and loading case files to mitigate arbitrary code execution risks.
- Implemented `CaseEncoder` and `case_decoder` in `pdfrecon/utils.py` to handle `pathlib.Path`, `datetime.datetime`, and `set` objects.
- Updated `pdfrecon/app_gui.py` to use `json.dump` for saving cases.
- Updated `pdfrecon/app_gui.py` to attempt `json.load` first when opening cases.
- Added fallback to `pickle.load` for legacy `.prc` files, but gated it behind a user confirmation dialog ("Legacy Format Warning").
- Added warning messages to `lang/translations.json`.
- Updated `_export_reader` to also use JSON serialization.

Co-authored-by: Rasmus-Riis <4140365+Rasmus-Riis@users.noreply.github.com>
